    • isKeywordsPatternsValid

      public boolean isKeywordsPatternsValid()
      This checks whether the keywords patterns in the json is valid. Each one of these must not be null! If any of them are null then this returns false.

    • checkNotNull

    • isColumnLengthsValid

      public boolean isColumnLengthsValid()
      This checks whether columns from the json is null meaning it is not defined. And checks whether 0 or -1 is in the list. If it is then this means this is a invalid list and should be considered null. And will return false.

    • isParserTokenLogicValid

      public boolean isParserTokenLogicValid()
      This checks whether the parser token logic is set and whether it is valid. A valid parser token logic must contain each part and each part must not be null. In the columns there must not be any negative numbers and if there is a 0 then it must be the only number in the columns list. If these conditions are not meet then this will return false.     • isRulerValid

      public boolean isRulerValid()
      This checks whether a ruler is valid. A ruler is not valid if it is null or contains a 0 or -1 number. If it is valid then this will also sort the arraylist.

    • isfullSplitColumnValid

      public boolean isfullSplitColumnValid()
      Checks whether fill split is not null meaning is is not defined in the json. If it is not defined in the json it returns false.

    • isfullSplitColumnAndcolumnLengthsSameSize

      public boolean isfullSplitColumnAndcolumnLengthsSameSize()
      checks whether full splitcolumn and columnlengths are the same size which is required. If they are not the same size then this returns false.
